                    <comment id="12926689" author="thetaphi" created="Sun, 31 Oct 2010 10:03:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;By the way, the whole loading in the TokenFilter is broken! XML files should never be load by a Reader, always by InputStream. The charset detection is part of the XML spec and the default is UTF-8 if not overridden in the XML file. The HyphenationCompoundWordTokenFilter supplies ISO-8859-1 as fixed for the reader, so it is never possible to load other xml files with different charsets. This is another issue, I will open for 3.x and trunk (as it needs API change).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12926697" author="thetaphi" created="Sun, 31 Oct 2010 12:13:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2732&quot; title=&quot;Fix charset problems in XML loading in HyphenationCompoundWordTokenFilter (also Solr&amp;#39;s loader from schema)&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-2732&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12926719" author="thetaphi" created="Sun, 31 Oct 2010 14:51:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2732&quot; title=&quot;Fix charset problems in XML loading in HyphenationCompoundWordTokenFilter (also Solr&amp;#39;s loader from schema)&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-2732&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
